						<summary>

						<p>Slab standing in the <hi rend="italic">Māvinakaṭṭe-hāḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sadāśivarāya, 1557 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to register a gift of money income as <hi rend="italic">uṁbaḷi</hi> from Bannāḍi in Voḍarase probably to god Nārāyaṇadēva of Koṭe-kēri by <hi rend="bold">Mallappoḍeya</hi> who was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya</hi> under the orders of <hi rend="bold">Sadāśivarāya-nāyaka</hi> of Keḷadi who was appointed as the governor of that terriotory, by the king.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1478</hi> (1479 current), <hi rend="bold">Naḷa, Māgha śu. 1, Thursday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1557 A.D., January 1.</hi> The weekday, however, was Friday.</p>						

						</summary>
